section.para:
The record expression {. K0 = E0 , … , Kn = En .} 
publishes the record {. K0 = v0 , … , Kn = vn .}
only if each expression Ei deflates to value vi. 
Otherwise, it halts silently.

The type of a record value {. K0 = v0 , … , Kn = vn .}
where vi has type Ti,
is a record type, written {. K0 :: T0 , … , Kn :: Tn .}.

example.programlisting:
{- Normalize a given integer vector using records -}

def magnitude(v) = 
  (v.x * v.x + 
   v.y * v.y + 
   v.z * v.z) ** 0.5
    >tot>
      tot ** (1.0/2)

def norm(v) = 
  val m = magnitude(v)
  {. x = v.x / m, 
     y = v.y / m, 
     z = v.z / m .}

val velocity = {. x = 3.0, y = 0.0, z = 4.0 .}      
norm(velocity) 

{-
OUTPUT:
{. x = 0.6, y = 0.0, z = 0.8 .}
-}

{- Add an alpha field to an rgb color record -}

val rgb = {. red = 60, green = 230, blue = 5 .}
val rgba = rgb + {. alpha = 128 .}
rgba.alpha

{-
OUTPUT:
128
-}
